Cucumber Notes
Cucumber will not interact with any browser or any API response
It is just a library used to adapt the BDD
BDD -> Behaviour Driver Development -> Its a development based process

QA/DEV/BA or Product Ownder --> 3 Amigo's

Common File --> Called Feature file : Scenario (test steps)
Its a collabaratrive approach --> Everyone needs to write the Feature file.
We Will be using keyword called --> Given, When and Then --> This is called Gherkin Language
It should be plain English

It is one of Library used to write the BDD --> Pom.xml

Feature File --> Step Definition (Java Code) --> Test Runner
// Step Definition --> Java Code which will be executed when the step is executed
// Test Runner --> It will run the feature file and step definition
The Extension of the feature file is .feature

Login.feature
--> Scenario: Login to the application
Given User is on the login page
When User enters username and password
And User clicks on the login button
Then User should be redirected to the home page
And Additional Assertions can be added here

--> Scenario Outline: Login to the application with different credentials
Given User is on the login page
When User enters username "<username>" and password "<password>"
Then User should be redirected to the home page
Examples:
| username | password |
| user1    | pass1    |
| user2    | pass2    |

Test Runner --> In Cucumber we will use JUnit or TestNG as a test runner

In BDD, we should avoid writing the test data in the excel file. Add everything in the feature file itself.
Add multiple cases and examples in the feature file using Scenario Outline and Examples.
